  "texts": [
    "We used semistructured interviews because they could shed light on pertinent real-world questions related to the study (Catterall, 2000; Maxwell, 2008).",
    "First, we designed a questionnaire and conducted two pilot interviews.",
    "From the interviews, we identified that the terms \"explainability\" and \"explainable recommendation\" are not widely used and, hence, not well known among users.",
    "It was noticed that participants in the sample interviews were having difficulty understanding what the terms mean.",
    "Therefore, we used some alternative and better-known terms such as \"reaso ning\"/\"hints\"/\"explanations\" while conducting the interviews."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We used semistructured interviews because they could shed light on pertinent real-world questions related to the study (Catterall, 2000; Maxwell, 2008)."
  ]
